<p>Disability insurance pays you a portion of your salary if you find yourself unable to work for medical reasons. Unlike worker&#39;s comp, disability insurance doesn&#39;t only apply when the injury/illness is work-related.</p>
<p>There are two kinds of disability insurance, short term and long term.</p>
<ul>
   <li>Short term doesn&#39;t kick in for a little while (often two weeks) after leaving work—for some plans, not until you run out of paid time off. You can generally stay on short term disability for a matter of months.</li>
   <li>Long term disability kicks in after you&#39;ve exhausted the short term disability option. Depending on your plan, you may be able to stay on long term disability for years—or at least until you reach age 65 and start social security.</li>
</ul>​​ 
