<h2>Glossary</h2>
<hr/>
<dl>
   <dt>Elimination period</dt>
   <dd>A required waiting period between when you are injured or diagnosed and when you start receiving benefits.</dd>
   <dt>Outpatient</dt>
   <dd>Someone who is receiving healthcare but isn&#39;t admitted to the hospital—they may still be treated at the hospital, but they don&#39;t require an overnight stay.</dd>
   <dt>Premium</dt>
   <dd>What you pay to have insurance. This is a set amount of money automatically withdrawn from each paycheck.</dd>
</dl>​
